her is bound to create this kind of confusion and disorganization. This was entirely my fault and again I hope you can all forgive me, but I was unavoidably pulled away, and my attempts to contact Molfious were unsuccessful. I should have thought to call on Belce but it did not occur to me.<br>
<br>
I would hate to see one set back like this derail our attempts at organizing large events. The key is always learn from the past and move on. Lets not put off planning more because of one bad outing.<br>
<br>
Perhaps we should have 2 people in on raid organization from the start so that in the event something like this happens we can recover more gracefully.<br>
<br>
Remember this happened to us once before when the raid organizer could not log on, and we suffered the same sort of trouble getting things going.<br>
<br>
In short lets suck it up, and move on. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#871f78><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/uwerzat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>werzat</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>has been run over by Dulcette</span><br> <font color=#0000FF>(1/2/02 2:27:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://werzat.freeservers.com/vincent.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forgive and move on...</span><hr size=1> I agree Lorne; I see no reason to stop holding large-scale events.  A lot of people got tremendously frustrated with how things were going and had you been there, Lorne, you would have suffered the same frustrations as the rest of us.  The mistakes that occured (the honest ones) are always there and that raid was just not gelling no matter what anyone did.<br>
