<br>
Sorry about not getting Thor in the chat group, I did know it was needed and tried a few times, hence forth all group leaders will be named Tom, Jill, Frank or other easy to spell name &lt;Yeah I said the words,... well sorta&gt; This bit here is an example of a time when it is a good thing to just sit down, not move until this is fixed, call your group leader on the floor and spam me with demands to get it fixed.  This one thing goes a long way in explaining what seriously fubar'd our efforts last night and that is entirely my error.  I was able to invite to the chat group, I knew it was needed, I just couldn't spell that name and did not take the time to get it. <br>
<br>
Some of the things we know that we need to improve is keeping our people together in areas where there are many others such as Mile Forts.  One of the things I do is pick someone in my group and make sure I find them and stay with them.  In this manner I insure that we get our group together in some good time, like the snowball effect. <br>
<br>
Initiative and team responsiblity<br>
<br>
I like initiative, people able to make a decision and move it forward without needing every step confirmed for them, I like seeing groups operate as an individual unit responsible to themselves first and foremost.  Having said this I would like us to hold back here at first while we get up to speed, lets pay attention to what we are all doing, do it all together and later we can extend a looser set of rules for engagement.  The important thing to realize is that the smallest unit is not the individual, but the group.  One person can not accomplish anything, one person trying to solo in a group is even worse. Your group is responsible for you and your solo efforts are going to endanger your groupmates.  Therefore while you are alone and getting ganked it doesn't affect anyone other than yourself.  When you are in a group doing this you have recklessly endangered the people that are committed to aid you.   Things that you might be expected to do is to uncover or bait the Middie healers so we can deal with them, this could hurt, don't think star quarterback or like that.  I want people that want to be on the best team and not best on team.  Don't look at your individual RP's but instead look at the guild RP's for a measure of success if you want. <br>
<br>
Communicating Information<br>
<br>
We all have a real job here to relay information as you get it.  The sooner we can all be on the same page the better, but to be helpful we need proper correct info.  Information needs to include at the very least a direction and a landmark so it can be placed.  Vague information is just as good as no information, pretending to be Paul Reevre yelling the Middies are coming is not helpful. A direction and location is the minimum needed, more is better.  You don't need to get it all out right away, just start with a heading, type and a landmark. &quot;Hibies NW of DC&quot;  Later you can add number and con if possible. <br>
<br>
