<br>
Yes there will be times when events in peoples lives interrupt plans they have made. Real life and/or virtual life for that matter, it just happens.<br>
<br>
I commend those that stepped in and tried to make the best out of an already difficult situtation, and I can understand peoples frustration.<br>
<br>
Remember, arguement and disagreement doesn't have to divide us, but rather it should challenge us and in the end bring us closer together. Through the use of effective discourse we all become better players and friends.<br>
<br>
So remember - try to take peoples criticisms and/or suggestions for what they are meant to be - an attempt to make us all better. <br>
<br>
At the same time, if you have a suggestion/cristism to make, say it in a constructive manner. In the end, we should be benifiting from these experiences even if they don't always go the way we want them to go. <br>
